column5: got out today with Lloyd  who as always shows off by getting more and bigger  fish then any one else I know he does it to bug me.....lol  we did a long run out and it was easy going the ride back I did by myself and didn't go as close to shore as I did on the way out and found a pressure crack I really didn't like. took a couple of km to find a nice spot to cross it..besides that it was a good ride
Damn, wish I could have made it  How's tomorrow sound??  Way to go Lloyd, some nice lakers there - showoff
Terry, how's the ice?  Didn't make it out today, but hoping for mid week... Really wanna bring the sled.
Nice Laker!!  This wind is definitely pushing the ice around  Rick

7" where  I was there are lots of small pressure cracks and one bad one ,I think it was north of long shoal  i hear the lake access at ibp has some broken ice..ok for skidoos but gave atv-ers a hard time
Dang Dude  Yah--you and Greg  Klatt--fellow OFNER  Well Done man   Sucks to be you-lol   Have FUN  Hope to see you @ the Fishing for Tyler gig Terry  Play Safe   Paul  www.lake-simcoe.ca
They are sure some nice fish!! wtg!!!!!!!!!!
Great looking greasers!!
nice fish
I showed up,but the sign said,left with out ya. LOL  Skunked two times now eh,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,You will get yer mojo back soon bud.
damn pin ruined me  lol
LOL  Word is,it,s open again,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
Im jealous... Havent had a chance to the ice yet
Friggin Lloyd and his trained fish act....
Almost looks like the same fish doesn't it
Nice catch guys. Now WHERE are the whities this season  ?!?  Cheers, Ice Fisherman
just bring several changes of clothing and you can be a luckiest fisherman all winter long too....nice shooting on the greasers
Lloyd is a magician on the ice. Third time is the charm Terry!!

Well like always I'm happy when you fish close to me Terry.  That sign I put down that says "My name is not Terry" always works great lol. This was a great day. Hit a few more fish while we were trying to pack up. Ill take lakers over whitefish for the fight any day of the week.  Ice is good but watch out for all the big cracks.
Ice is good for sleds but the cracks are no way for bikes. 6" of Ice under my hut today. Another week of cold should be great
That's what I was thinking   haha. Great fishing guys!
Damm that's some nice fish right there.
Appreciate the updates guys, good show out there!
Very respectable Laker! Hope that Simcoe keeps getting ice for you fellas, seems to be producing well lately!
